This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it addresses the problem of object detection from RGB-D data. Additionally, the paper mentions applications such as robot grasping and autonomous driving, which are closely related to robotics (cs.RO). The use of attention-based models and deep learning techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of visualizations and improved feature representation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
